MLflow works fine with nginx, in the following configuration also offload the static file serving part to nginx:

```
        location /static-files/ {
            alias MLFLOW_DIR_PATH/server/js/build/;
            try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
            include /usr/lib/mlflow/startup_scripts/nginx/conf/static_file.conf;
        }

        location / {
            proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000;
        }
```

Hey Guys, I Think i have a new one for you, havent found a solution anywhere else. When accessing the ui outside of the reverse proxy it works fine. but inside the through the iframe in our ui the proxy gives the following. 

<img width="777" alt="Screen Shot 2021-06-22 at 12 25 43 PM" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/80490024/122964773-9c20ac80-d355-11eb-8180-1302f147831c.png">


for refrence here is our proxy code:

```
      location /mlflow/ {
        resolver kube-dns.kube-system.svc.cluster.local valid=5s;
        set $mlflowUpstream "mlflow";

        proxy_pass "http://$mlflowUpstream.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:80/";
        sub_filter '/ajax-api' '/mlflow/ajax-api';
        sub_filter '/static-files' '/mlflow/static-files';
        sub_filter_once off;
        sub_filter_types *;
      }
```

is there a way to ignore the bootstrap integrity without directly accessing the source code?
